<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="faq-header">
    <div class="section-label" style="text-align:center;">FAQ</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align:center;">Common questions, <em>honest answers</em></h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I really need an estate plan if I'm young and healthy?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Absolutely. Estate planning isn't just about death — it includes powers of attorney and healthcare directives that protect you if you become incapacitated. If you have children, a home, or any assets, you need an estate plan now.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the difference between a will and a trust?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>A will takes effect at death and must go through Arizona's probate process — which is public and court-supervised. A trust takes effect immediately, avoids probate, is private, and can manage your assets during your lifetime. Most Arizona families benefit from having both.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does estate planning cost?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>We offer transparent flat-fee pricing. You'll receive an exact quote after your free consultation — no hourly surprises, ever. Basic will packages and comprehensive trust-based plans are priced based on your specific needs.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long does the process take?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Most clients complete their estate plan within 2–4 weeks. The process involves a free consultation, document drafting, a review meeting, and a signing appointment. We can expedite if needed.</p></div></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-btn" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do you serve clients outside of Mesa?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. We serve clients throughout the East Valley including Chandler, Gilbert, Tempe, Queen Creek, and Scottsdale. We also offer virtual consultations for clients anywhere in Arizona.</p></div></div>
